{"id": "duc04-testb-38:8#25", "contents": "The situation has been exacerbated by Turkey's massing of troops on the Syrian border and its readiness to conduct cross-border raids to eradicate what it claims are guerrilla bases harboring Kurdish rebels. Syria has denied these allegations, and similar accusations made by Turkish officials against Greece in the past have been met with denials and a lack of evidence. The strained relations between Greece and Turkey are nothing new, with the two NATO allies having come close to war twice in the past 11 years over the Aegean Sea."}
